      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm trying to build this little tool to find flaky tests in our CI pipeline. basically i need a function `detect_flakiness(func, n_runs=10)` that returns True if the function output changes between runs, and False if it's consistent.\n\nheres the test i'm running it against to check if it works:\n\n```python\nimport random\n\ndef flaky_test():\n    # sometimes returns 1, sometimes 0\n    return random.choice([0, 1])\n\ndef stable_test():\n    # always returns 0\n    return 0\n\ndef always_fails_test():\n    # always returns 0, but we treat it as \"stable\" \n    # because it's deterministic (even if it's a bad test)\n    return 0\n\n# The detector should see flaky_test as True (flaky)\n# and stable_test/always_fails_test as False (not flaky)\nassert detect_flakiness(flaky_test, n_runs=20) == True\nassert detect_flakiness(stable_test, n_runs=20) == False\nassert detect_flakiness(always_fails_test, n_runs=20) == False\n\nprint(\"All tests passed!\")\n```\n\ncan u write the `detect_flakiness` function for me?",
