      "content": "Here is the `detect_flakiness` function you requested. It executes the provided function repeatedly and checks if the set of results contains more than one unique value. If there is more than one unique result among the runs, the test is considered flaky and the function returns `True`.\n\n```python\ndef detect_flakiness(func, n_runs=10):\n    results = [func() for _ in range(n_runs)]\n    return len(set(results)) > 1\n```",
